Combine ontology chunks as node-ed-node triples. Preserve original nodes and edges, adding new links to connect concepts across chunks. Use meaningful edge labels describing relationships (e.g., "typeOf" or "partOf"). Identify semantically related concepts to create a cohesive ontology. Avoid redundant or less informative edges, and introduce new nodes to improve coherence.
Input format:
Chunk 1:
C1A,rel1,C1B
C1B,rel2,C1C
Chunk 2:
C2A,rel3,C2B
C2C,rel4,C2D
Chunk 3:
...
Output a unified ontology in this format:
Orig1,OrigRel,Orig2
Isolated,NewRel,Existing
AnotherOrig,OrigRel,RelatedOrig
NewConcept,ConnectingRel,LinkedConcept
Ensure the output includes original nodes and edges, and new semantic relationships linking concepts across chunks. Use Triplet-like format.